<seg id=1> Chinese Building Materials Industry Developing Quickly Through Outward Cooperation </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, March 19th, reporter Li Jianmin.  The Chinese building materials industry views the enforcement of cooperation with the outside as an important method of accelerating development, as the realm of utilizing foreign capital is quickly expanding.  To date, the entire industry has attracted foreign investment totaling US$5 billion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> A chief official with the National Building Materials Bureau revealed today, while granting an interview, that presently a large number of cement engineering construction projects are funded by loans from the World Bank and the Asia Bank.  Projects such as Tongling, of Anhui, and Xiangxiang, of Hunan, have already gotten underway. </seg>
<seg id=4> Foreign investments are rapidly being utilized to enhance elements of building materials science, such as the creation of new materials as well as new techniques and methods of production. </seg>
<seg id=5> Upscale hygiene porcelain and ceramics technical upgrading project, which is developed by utilizing a US$100 million preferential export fund from Italy, is developing in Shanxi, Shandong, Guangdong, Jilin Hunan, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Recently, the Chinese building materials industry in conjunction with governmental organizations, as well as multi-national corporations of Holland, Germany, Thailand, Greece, Australia, Japan, France, Denmark, etc., signed mutual cooperation agreements which have had significant positive impacts on partnership. </seg>
<seg id=7> Last year the export volume of Chinese building materials exceeded US$2.1 billion. exported 12 million tons of cement, which is 46% higher than that of last year, and hit the best record. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> In addition, in recent years China has also adopted the practice from abroad of utilizing production lines of "pre-decompositional kiln" and established series of large modern cement enterprises such as Jidong, Ningguo, Huaihai, Liuzhou, etc, which have increased the annual production capacity to 22 million tons. </seg>
</p>
